Top Stories (March 1)

CALIFORNIA GOVERNOR EXPECTS TO REACH POWER-LINES AGREEMENT WITH SECOND UTILITY
California Gov. Gray Davis said Tuesday he expected the state to reach an 
agreement to buy power lines from Pacific Gas & Electric Co., but it could 
take up to a month -- a delay that might hamper the state's ability to secure 
power for anticipated shortfalls this summer.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/03/01/krtbn/0000-0347-SJ-POWER-DEAL

CALIFORNIA ISO REQUESTS CONTINUED CONSERVATION EFFORTS; STAGE TWO ELECTRICAL 
EMERGENCY DECLARED THIS MORNING
The California Independent System Operator declared a Stage Two Electrical 
Emergency this morning, Thursday, March 1, 2001 at 6:50 a.m.
